    # [Scene: Rooftop Nursery | Dusk]

    scene bg ch15_8943bc_1 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The soft creak of rope, distant gulls, water lapping faintly against old stone.]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Low, steady cello; a slow pulse underlining each breath.]
    "You feel Elias's hand find yours beneath the worn bench the way a tide finds a familiar inlet — quietly, with the inevitability of habit. His fingers curl around yours, warm despite the sea chill. The contact is small and ordinary and carries the weight of half a dozen compromises."
    show elias_kahn at left:
        zoom 0.7

    elias_kahn "We keep the audit logs open, we staff the citizen monitors, and we don't let them wave off the corridor clauses. Nights like this, I remember why we did it."
    "You answer with a laugh that tastes like copper and rain. It's softer than it once would have been; it has margins now, small breaks where worry lives."
    show maya_corvin at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_corvin "We hold them to it. We grit our teeth and hold the lines."

    elias_kahn "We do it together. Even when I'm in committee rooms and three time zones away."
    "You let the word together sit between you, warm and fragile. Years fold over that tiny exchange like a thin, weathered tarp: patched, necessary."
    hide elias_kahn
    hide maya_corvin

    scene bg ch15_8943bc_2 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: The cello continues; a single piano note drops and lingers.]
    "You think back — not to the day of vote tallies, but to the slow, bureaucratic nights that followed: the citizen audits that spat up errors and then corrected them; the quarterly hearings where community speakers"
    "were allowed two minutes, then four; the municipal memos that used the word 'corridor' like an act of faith. The victories were small and legally contingent. The losses were visible and stubborn."

    scene bg ch15_8943bc_3 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Footsteps, market chatter, the metallic ping of a sensor uploading data.]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: A restrained build into mid-tempo strings.]
    "You stand and walk the nursery aisles. Rafi moves beside you, hands forever marked with soil; his voice is the same gravelly comfort it always was."
    show rafi_odeh at left:
        zoom 0.7

    rafi_odeh "Grafting's going smoother. The new sedge beds survived the spring surge. Kids are learning to stitch the roots to the mats."
    show maya_corvin at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_corvin "Did you patch the eastern row like I asked?"

    rafi_odeh "Three nights ago. We lost two mats last winter, but the buffer held where you convinced them to leave the inlet alone."
    "You let your fingers hover over a tray of sedge cuttings. They are small, stubborn things — the neighborhood's slow protest against a steel coastline."

    menu:
        "Trace a sedge sprout with your thumb":
            "You lift a damp sprout, soil crumbed under your thumbnail. The touch steadies you; for a moment the grief becomes a practical plan."
        "Fold the audit packet into your jacket":
            "You slide the audit packet close to your chest like a talisman. The paper is thin but dense with obligations and obligations are a kind of armor."

    # --- merge ---
    "Rafi watches you with a look that has learned to read the tiny tells of fatigue."

    rafi_odeh "Don't let the packet sit too long. The independent board wants us to present monthly numbers now. They like numbers more than faces, but you know faces make the numbers matter."
    "You think of Lio two alleys over, painting a new face on a wall. The mural's paint peels in places where the tide crosses too often; in other places it thrives. Lio's grin when you walk"
    "by is quick and a little reckless — the city's youth refusing to be only inventory."
    # [Scene: Reworked Promenade | Morning]
    hide rafi_odeh
    hide maya_corvin

    scene bg ch15_8943bc_4 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Wind threading through reeds; a distant municipal siren that no longer makes you jump the way it once did.]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: A patient mid-tempo rhythm, strings that hum like a steady warning.]
    "You walk the boardwalk that used to be entirely drowned some seasons ago. The engineered sections are new, sharp-edged, and unavoidable. The living sections are stitched in with careful hands. Where the two meet, the seams look raw."
    show elias_kahn at left:
        zoom 0.7

    elias_kahn "There was a clause they tried to shove through. I stalled it — long vote, messy hearings. I called in favors."
    show maya_corvin at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_corvin "Favors that owed you political capital."

    elias_kahn "We trade currency we have. You taught me that. But it was ugly. They keep pushing to standardize the designs. Means more precedent."
    "You listen, fingers finding the compass in your pocket. The compass doesn't point anymore; it only sits and keeps you company. You have learned to navigate without a true north that is predictable."

    elias_kahn "Listen — Lio's mural at Dock Three? It's gone viral. Mayor's office is sending a crew to discuss cultural preservation funding."

    maya_corvin "Or to sanitize it."

    elias_kahn "Maybe both. We'll be there. Together."
    "The word both tastes like a bargain and bitterness in the same mouth."

    menu:
        "Point out the erosion under the living breakwater":
            "You point to the darkened sod where the mats have scoured. Elias follows your finger, his jaw tightening as he registers the failure; he already has three memos in mind."
        "Ask Elias about his next trip":
            "You ask about his travel schedule. He sighs, listing committee dates like a litany. The distance between planning rooms and porches shows up in the calendar he hands you in lieu of an answer."

    # --- merge ---
    "You both stand and watch a group of volunteers, young and old, press sandbags and weave root mats. Their rhythm is purposeful. Their faces are lined with long seasons. You feel gratitude and a hollow that neither cancels."
    # [Scene: Market Stalls | Noon]
    hide elias_kahn
    hide maya_corvin

    scene bg ch15_8943bc_5 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Bargaining voices, the clip-click of a tablet updating tide alerts, a child laughing.]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Subtle percussion; heartbeat-like, steady.]
    show lio_corvin at left:
        zoom 0.7

    lio_corvin "You look like you carried the tide on your shoulders. Sit, eat. The pickled beans are on me."
    show maya_corvin at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_corvin "If I sit, who will hold the hearing notes?"

    lio_corvin "You taught me the short list. You'll do it in your sleep."
    "You sit anyway. The market is small joy hammered into survival. Conversation turns to the upcoming independent board hearing: a ritual of accountability born from a compromise you pushed for. It will convene in two days. They will shuffle documents. They will call witnesses."
    show rafi_odeh at center:
        zoom 0.7

    rafi_odeh "We have contingencies. The audit feed's public now. Citizens can flag deviations. It's not perfect, but it's something."
    "You nod. The something is at once a lifeline and a reminder of distance from the perfect solution you once envisioned."
    # [Scene: Independent Board Hearings | Afternoon]
    hide lio_corvin
    hide maya_corvin
    hide rafi_odeh

    scene bg ch15_8943bc_6 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Murmured questions, the scratch of pens, a clock that insists on time even when hearts do not.]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Low strings; tension built into a steady, mid-level hum.]
    "You sit at the front, the packet of citizen entries in a neat stack. Kai Navarro is in the room — not an adversary in armor today but a consultant with her corporate sigil traded for"
    "a civic placard. She meets your eyes with a look that is unreadable: not hostility exactly, but a balance of obligation and a strategic reserve."

    "Camila 'Kai' Navarro" "We complied with the corridor design. We allowed the wetlands pockets. The models show system-level resilience gains. But maintenance needs capital. You understand that."
    show maya_corvin at left:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_corvin "Maintenance is a promise — and promises need teeth. Your firm will sign the oversight protocol."

    "Camila 'Kai' Navarro" "Protocol, yes. Audit windows, public dashboards. I do not apologize for scale. Scale is survival, Maya."

    maya_corvin "Scale that takes without listening is the kind that repeats its own failures."

    "Camila 'Kai' Navarro" "Neither of us gets to keep everything. We get to decide what is worth hardening and what we let live and flex. That's engineering as ethics."

    maya_corvin "Then sign the clause that prevents unilateral recalibration. Public oversight. Citizen veto."
    "The room breathes. The clerk reads the motion aloud. Numbers flicker on a screen. The vote will be close. Years of paperwork, protests, grafted sedge, and sleepy committee nights compress into the sound of a projector clicking."
    "Elias Kahn places a gentle hand on the small of your back — a private support that steadies you in public."
    show elias_kahn at right:
        zoom 0.7

    elias_kahn "We hold them to it. We watch. We litigate if we must."

    "Camila 'Kai' Navarro" "Don't make me the villain here, Maya. The city needs protection before another season takes roofs."

    maya_corvin "And the city needs wetlands before there's nothing left to protect. We keep the living channels alive."
    "The vote is cast. The tally is a long breath. The motion carries by a narrow margin. There is applause and a subdued, almost stunned relief."
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Understated resolution; the mid-tempo strings retain a bruise of unease.]
    "You exit the hearing later, exhausted in that particular way that roots in the stomach. People congratulate you, press small packets into your hands — sandwiches, petitions, notes. Lio has painted a mural outside the hall: hands holding a seedling beneath a hard hat."
    # [Scene: Reworked Promenade | High Tide, Evening]
    hide maya_corvin
    hide elias_kahn

    scene bg ch15_8943bc_7 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: A steady, insistent tide. The sensors chirp with updates — tide, salinity, wave energy.]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: The cello returns; steady, mid-tempo. The music swells subtly, then holds.]
    "You stand at the rail. The ocean is unrepentant and honest about its work. You place your palm on the brass of the compass and feel only the cold of metal and the warmth of your"
    "own skin. The needle is as still as it has always been; the object is now talisman rather than tool."
    "Rafi Odeh arrives with a thermos of bitter coffee. He hands it to you without ceremony."
    show rafi_odeh at left:
        zoom 0.7

    rafi_odeh "We'll keep the monitoring shifts. New volunteers signed up. Lio's kids are part of the graft team now."
    "You look out at a patch of marsh where the sedge mats are thinner than they used to be. Half of the corridor is intact; the other half shows fresh scour lines where last week's surge cut deeper than models predicted."
    show maya_corvin at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_corvin "We learned something. We can adapt. But we also lost things we can't put back."
    show elias_kahn at center:
        zoom 0.7

    elias_kahn "We didn't lose everything."
    "You force a smile that doesn't reach your eyes. The balance between what you saved and what you yielded is a ledger you cannot close."
    "Camila 'Kai' Navarro appears at the promenade's far end, hands tucked in her coat pockets. She nods once — a small, private concession between strategists who have both loved and battered the same coastline."

    "Camila 'Kai' Navarro" "The oversight clause will make the difference if you keep pushing. Don't let it roll into habit."

    maya_corvin "Habit is how things die. Vigilance is how they continue."

    "Camila 'Kai' Navarro" "Then keep measuring."
    "Her departure is quick and clinical. It leaves you with a residue of weary respect."
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: A subtle build — the mid-arousal rising gently to a final emotional crest.]
    "You turn the compass over in your hand. It is small, dented, stitched with a cord that has been re-knotted more times than you can count. You remember a younger version of yourself who believed a"
    "plan could be fair and whole. You remember nights when you argued until your voice was a raw wire. You remember Lio's paint on your sleeve, Rafi's calm, Elias’s patient compromises, Kai’s relentless pragmatism."
    "You realize the romance that once burned like a bonfire has become a slow, deliberate practice. Elias's hands touch your shoulder more often than they hold it; your schedules synchronize around board meetings and tide events"
    "instead of long, aimless afternoons. There is love here — durable, uneven, threaded through policy memos and midnight audits — but it carries the same bruise as everything else: the cost of imperfect victories."
    "You press the compass to your chest and let the cold settle. There is a sharpness in your chest — a hollow that is not only sorrow but also discipline. The work will not end. The"
    "city's shoreline will demand maintenance, rethinking, and argument until the day the city no longer breathes."
    hide rafi_odeh
    hide maya_corvin
    hide elias_kahn

    scene bg ch15_8943bc_8 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The tide sighs. A distant child shouts, the call echoing over the water.]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Strings draw a final, restrained chord — melancholic, steady.]
    "You set the compass down on the railing and rest your hand over it. The gesture is small, ritualistic: a promise to guard what's left even when the cost remains high."
    show elias_kahn at left:
        zoom 0.7

    elias_kahn "We do it because if we don't, no one will."
    show maya_corvin at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_corvin "Because letting it go quietly is worse."
    "The two of you watch the tide fold itself into the harbor, and the boardwalk lights blink on one by one like reluctant stars. Lio's mural gleams in the lamplight, bright and ragged and refusing to"
    "be tidy. Rafi counts volunteers on his tablet. The sensor feeds stream into a public dashboard that citizens refresh like prayers."
    "You hold your palm on the compass. You think of the ground lost and what you kept, of the legal scaffolds that now hold half the living things, of the ways love has been rewired into"
    "nightly check-ins and shared folders. The mood inside you is heavy with loss and a resolve that has teeth."
    hide elias_kahn
    hide maya_corvin

    scene bg ch15_8943bc_9 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Fade to a single, held cello note that resolves into quiet.]
    "You breathe. There is closure, but it is the kind that tastes of salt and used bandages. You do not call this a victory. You do not call it a complete defeat. It is what remains"
    "after both have been counted: a community that endures in a remade shape; governance that learned to bend; a love that persists as practice rather than proclamation."

    scene bg ch15_8943bc_10 at full_bg
